HELP_TEXT =
    {app_name} {version} — {app_full_name}

    Usage:
      {app_name} <command> [options]

    Commands:
      encrypt, e     Encrypt a file or stdin
      decrypt, d     Decrypt a file
      templates, tpl List all available templates
      help, h        Show this help

    Global options:
      -h, --help     Show help
      -v, --verbose  Verbose output

    Encrypt/decrypt options:
      -f, --file <path>        Input file path (required)
      -o, --output <path>      Output file path (auto-generated if empty)
      -k, --key <password>     Password (mutually exclusive with --keyfile)
      -K, --keyfile <path>     32-byte key file (mutually exclusive with --key)
      -p, --process <chain>    Opcode chain (hex space-separated)
      -t, --template <ID>      Template ID (from templates.json)
      --template-file <path>   Custom template JSON file

    Split mode options:
      -s, --split              Enable split mode (.hdr + .dat)
      -H, --header <path>      Header file path (default header.hdr)
      -D, --data <path>        Data file path (default data.dat)

    Example chains:
      -p "08 06 0E 01 0F 00"    Standard password encryption
      -p "10 0A 11 00"          Compression + key file encryption
      -t 01                     Use predefined template

    Templates format (templates.json):
      {
        "01": "08 06 0E 01 0F 00",
        "02": "10 0A 11 00"
      }

    Examples:
      {app_name} encrypt -f my.txt -k 123456 -p "08 06 0E 01 0F 00"
      {app_name} decrypt -f my.bin -o out.txt -k 123456
      {app_name} templates

    See README for more.